MUSHROOM POISONING - UKRAINE
****************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Fri 25 Jun 2010
Source: RBC-Ukraine [in Russian, trans. Corr.ATS, edited]
<http://www.rbc.ua/rus/newsline/show/g-rozhkov-v-ukraine-s-nachala-goda-zafiksirovano-9-smertelnyh-25062010152600>


The deputy minister of health of Ukraine has announced that there have been
9 deaths due to mushroom poisoning in Ukraine since the beginning of the
year [2010]. The overall number of poisonings so far is 44 including 5
children. Most cases have been reported from Donetsk, Odessa, Khmelnytsky,
and Luhansk regions.

The deputy minister also added that 44 outbreaks of botulism have occurred
this year [2010] in Ukraine involving 62 people.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed-rus@promedmail.org>

[Unfortunately we have no information about the type of mushroom or
mushrooms involved in these 9 deaths. Let us hope there are no others for
the remainder of the year. - Mod.TG

The regions (oblasts) mentioned above can be see on the map of Ukraine at
<http://www.infoukes.com/ua-maps/oblasts/>. The HealthMap/ProMED-mail
interactive map of Ukraine is available at <http://healthmap.org/r/00Xn>. -
Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
